---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: "About Brainard's Greenscapes | Las Cruces Landscaping"
description: "Meet David Brainard — owner, designer, and installer behind Las Cruces' top-rated landscaping company. 19+ years of hands-on work in the Mesilla Valley."
---

<!-- Hero -->
<section class="bg-green-950 text-white py-16 md:py-24">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <p class="text-green-300 font-semibold text-sm uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">About Us</p>
    <h1 class="font-heading text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold mb-6">About {{ site.name }}</h1>
    <p class="text-green-100 text-lg max-w-2xl">Owner-operated landscaping in Las Cruces since 2007. When you call, David answers. When you meet on-site, David's there. When the work starts, David's on the job.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Meet David -->
<section class="py-16 bg-white">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
    <div>
      <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Meet David Brainard</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-4">David started {{ site.name }} in 2007 with a simple idea: show up when you say you will, do the work right, and treat every yard like it's your own. Nearly two decades later, that hasn't changed.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">He's the one who answers your call. He's the one who walks your property with you, listens to what you want, and tells you what'll actually work in the Las Cruces heat. And he's the one on-site making sure the job gets done the way he promised.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">That's the difference between hiring a company and hiring David. You're not getting passed off to a salesperson or a crew you've never met. You're working directly with the owner — from the first conversation to the final walkthrough.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <img src="/assets/images/brainards-landscape-maintenance-4.webp"
           alt="Brainard's Greenscapes landscape project in Las Cruces"
           width="548" height="540"
           loading="lazy"
           class="rounded-xl shadow-lg w-full">
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

